    "body": "## fix(ui): z= and tselect stop working\r\n\r\nProblem:\r\nAfter 55ceb31,  z= and tselect don't work if `vim.ui.select` is an async provider (especially terminal buffers).\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\nDrop the `vim.wait()` approach, use an async approach.\r\n\r\nfix #39506\r\n\r\n## feat(ui): use vim.ui.select for :oldfiles, :recover\r\n\r\nProblem:\r\n`:oldfiles` and swapfile `:recover` do not delegate to `vim.ui.select`.\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\n- Delegate to `vim.ui.select`.\r\n- Fix a long-standing `recover_names` bug where `concat_fnames(dir_name, files[i], true)` produced malformed `<dir>//<dir>/<file>` paths (also fixes `swapfilelist()`).\r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-30T17:42:53Z",
